< review>
Always one of the best. Love the atmosphere, especially since the remodel several years ago. The floor tiles are stunning. And the patio is a dream come true. You can't tell you're in the middle of the city with all the trees and water fountains. There's heaters and fans, plus strung lights so it can be used all year round.

My favorite is breakfast. They have great cocktails like lavender lemon drop, Irish coffee, and a mimosa carafe with different fruit purees. Great for a group.

I've always had great service. We have gone for their Easter brunch several years now and it is always wonderful. Especially if you can score a seat on the patio. Would highly recommend!</review>

There food is always so good which I am so grateful for because it is the best environment. They have done such an excellent job of creating a beautiful environment oasis to brunch in. The lemon lavender drop was the best drink I have ever had, but I felt it a lot more than expected so if you are a lightweight with me either share with a friend or eat a lot of bread.

<text>A group of four of us, celebrating 2 anniversaries, went tonight for dinner.  We got there early enough to get patio seating, which is first come basis.  I've always been a Paragarys fan, 20 years.  This was the first time I've been in about 3 years.  The menu didn't excite me, but I'm assuming they've limited it due to covid uncertainty. When looking at the menu I could not visualize what more than half the entrees would look like.  We each got a salad, mine was the butter lettuce beet.  It tasted dry, couldn't taste any dressing.  I ordered the spagettini.  I asked the waiter to describe it, it was dressed with butter and olive oil he said.  It came out with maybe a cup of pasta, about one crab leg worth of crab meat, and I could not tell it had butter and olive oil on it at all, it was very dry.  When I got home home I was still hungry.  There were a lot of serving staff, but I had to ask for everything and wait a long time to get it.  Granted, they were very busy but with staff just standing around.....<//text><user>109102168937267302811</user>< pics>

<user_name>Andrew Harlow</user_name><date>1595214434072<//date><Rating>5<//Rating>< Review>
Mushroom salad and sparkling Rose were so good.<//Review>
<pictures>None< /pictures><Resp>None<//Resp><gmap_id>0x809ad0eb74931c33:0xcbd9102b5e05bdcf<//gmap_id></record></dataset><record>
< review>
Made reservations for this restaurant for 7:45pm yesterday for my boyfriend and myself. I requested outdoor seating since they have patio dining. When we arrived, the hostess knew that I requested outdoor but didn't mention it at all. I asked if we were sitting on the patio and she said that even though she saw that she didn't have anything. I had to ask before she acknowledged it. It was going to be at least 35 minutes before we could sit outside so we opted to eat inside. They put us at the smallest table in the entire dining room that was shoved up against a pillar. I immediately went into an anxiety attack. There is supposed to be 6 feet between people but the other table was no more than 3 feet behind me with people at it. Mind you, the rest of the restaurant is EMPTY. Every table was bigger than ours and had 2 people at them as well. The waitress came by and asked what we would like to drink. My other half asked for Sprite and I was ok with water, which she said she was bringing. Sprite came and I had to ask for the water. She said she forgot. We were given cold, hard bread and butter. The water finally came and we ordered. I ordered whole wheat spagettini and my boyfriend ordered the rigatoni. The menu states there is summer squash and roasted cherry tomato in the spaghettini. I had 3 not roasted cherry tomatoes, and strips of zucchini and yellow squash that were no thicker than the spaghetti noodles. There were about 5 pine nuts and no parmesan. Seriously, for $20 you couldn't actually put squash in it? Or actually roast a cherry tomato? My boyfriend got his dish and there was about a tablespoon of sausage in the plate. It really looked sad. We only saw our server one more time without having to flag her down.
Hands down it was the worst dining experience I have had in quite some time. I do not recommend this place at all. My dish was overpriced and underwhelming. I can cook the same dish at home and will.< /review>

<pictures>None</pictures><Review>We had a great experience here. This was a perfect date spot, casual enough that there is not a dress code but has an upscale feel to it.

Cocktails are about $15, and an entree is between $20-40. For the environment and service, I thought the prices were reasonable.

Despite the table next to us being completely rude to her, our server never ceased to be pleasant. She was timely, knowledgeable and happy to recommend cocktails to us (all were delicious)

The food is why this got a four star instead of five. The meatball app was dry. The rest of the food was tasty and the portions were great. The only exceptional plate was the pork though.

I would happily come back here, it's perfect for dates, birthday dinners, work functions, etc.</Review><Time>1544049572513<//Time><rate>4< /rate></record></dataset><record>

< Review>
A lovely brunch spot with a tranquil outdoor area. Don't let the Sacramento summer heat keep you from enjoying the patio which is covered and complete with a peaceful water feature. Should you come during a chillier season the interior and bar are lovely as well.

The brunch menu is simple and hits all the staples from a breakfast burrito to lemon-ricotta pancakes, and avocado toast. Prices are about average with the avocado toast coming in at $15 and cocktails about $13.

The staff is attentive and helpful especially if you are having trouble deciding what to get. While there isn't a private lot there is a lot of street parking.< /Review>

< review>
I dined here for the first time in Valentine night and made reservations two weeks prior. The Valentine menu was released without vegetarian main coarse and I gave the restaurant a prompt call and Sophie quickly talked to the Chef and he offered to make a vegetarian meal for me that night that was off of the regular menu. This is just one example of the level of customer service provided by this establishment. Our waiter Niah was also amazing and fixed a wobbly table the second we sat and she noticed the problem. Customer Service aside, the food was outstanding. The Artichoke soup had a perfect viscosity and wasn't too creamy, the Fettuccine pasta with pesto couldn't have been made better, and passion fruit sorbet on the Panna Cotta was something I had never tasted before. Overall very satisfied with the experience here and anticipate coming back to dine once again.

Edit "July 6th, 2020"
Ordered takeout today with high hopes of a delicious meal, a $30 Pizza and a $27 Chicken Dish. There was tension in the room between customer service during the transaction, and it felt nothing like our previous review and experience. Pizza was subpar, cracker like dough that was over charred uniformly around the circumference. Chicken dish was slightly too heavy on the sweet side as well. This was not as expected and thus my review reflects the average of the 5 star and today's experience, sitting now at 3 stars. I hope to return and have a better dining experience.<//review>

114341484518322384514< /user_id>
<Gmap_id>0x809ad0eb74931c33:0xcbd9102b5e05bdcf<//Gmap_id>< Review>
Went here for mothers day and sat outside.
Ambience, setting: The place really looks awesome. The open air design of the restaurant connecting to the outer patio somehow just makes you feel more comfortable. The patio area is also very green and closed off from the street, so it creates its own little world. Also there are fans to keep you cool.
Definitely a spot to go for summer if youre looking for a great atmosphere.

Food:
-pastries they gave for appetizers were a win- moist, sweet and not dry.
-Smoked trout on toast was a winner.
-Strawberries with bellwether farm ricotta- the cheese on top had no flavor unfortunately so was odd, but the strawberries and the rest were great.
-Dungeness Crab scramble- crab in eggs was okay, we thought it could have used more salt.
-Eggs benedict- this one probably was the best loved the ham+egg on biscuit with spinach.
Also everyone loved the potatoes that came with their plates- crunchy texture and soft on the inside with not too much salt.</Review>

<Rate>5</Rate>< review>
Great way lace for date night with my wife. The atmosphere was beautiful inside and felt like you are in someone‚Äôs dining room (in the best way). It‚Äôs a little noisy, but the tables are small with enough space that my wife and I could hold a conversation just fine.

Great food. I had the steak special and my wife had the half chicken. Both were perfect, juicy, and cooked just right. The tomato soup was unbelievably good (and incidentally vegan) and the pear and endive salad was deliciously sweet. Even the potatoes and chard that came with my meal weee perfect and delicious. Plus, even with drinks, a salad, soup, main entree, and desert (for 2) it was around $100. Not too bad of a price and well worth every penny. I have paid much more for meals that were not nearly as good or satisfying.

Will definitely be back.< /review>

<Review>Expected my favorite appetizer, calamari, yet it was not on the menu.  My dish of beef, asked for medium raw, arrived raw with the outside too cooked.  Chewy like beef jerky texture.

I like Paragary but was not happy not only about my dish but the salmon was noticeably not "fine dining" standard.  Any cook knows to prepare fish,  which two at our table ordered should be evenly cut for even cooking.  My husband's salmon was raw too in the middle.

Normally my husband likes salt in his food...he commented his mashed potato was salty.  I told him both my potato and kale were loaded with too much salt.  Luckily the waiter offered more bread.  It was how the vegetables were eaten, otherwise my plate would have looked barely half eaten.

Not sure why, the lights were turned down very low... a challenge to read the menu and see the food we were eating.  Normally I photograph the food to share with family and friends.  I did not want to ask them to turn up the lights.  Suggestion:  place a small table light or candle if the desire is a "romantic" ambience.

Like other comments pricey menu.  I like good food but when the portion is compartively small to the high price and average kitchen preparation, it is questionable.

Question is:  Would we go there again...?< /Review>< Pictures>
None< /Pictures>

< review>
This is a restaurant that has GREAT food and I cannot understand why they are not busy all the time. Their outside patio is so relaxing and they have a huge back bar outside as well. their food is really good and their menu changes with the seasons. The wait staff is very friendly and do a good job - but sometimes they seem short-staffed and it means waiting for your food - but that's ok because you can buy wine by the bottle and enjoy wine and conversation with your friends while you wait. One bartender Shayna is awesome and she is quick - especially if you sit at the bar. AND they now have a loyalty card - so you know I will be back!<//review>

<userid>116519304153514337403< /userid><Rating>5< /Rating>< Text>
Outdoor seating is really nice! The food is good tooüëç< /Text>

<user>116053095629219655089</user>< Review>
We visited on Valentine's day, with a reservation. They were swamped. It took 25 minutes past our reservation time to be seated, and the host was in defensive mode, so was in no state to listen or pay attention to reservation details. Definitely speak up if something isn't right, or they may not notice.

The food was okay. No dish was outstanding, though you could tell what they were going for with the entree, a perfectly cooked buttery cod filet next to a beach of forbidden rice, and a sea of... brackish soy sauce water in which swam pale rubbery and bland things with monotone yet not subtle flavor profiles. The Oyster Rockefeller amuse bouche was nice and hot, and the pavlova dessert was intensely LEMON. Not a single course was perfect, and the meal as a whole was not satisfying.

Overall, the bill came to $300 for 2 people, so I'd say it was a bad value for the money at an event like this. We've had good experiences here in previous years, on other events than Valentine's. Maybe V-Day made everyone more stressed and frantic than usual, but it left a lasting bad taste in our mouths.<//Review>

<response>None<//response><userid>106149036596342442791</userid><Rating>3</Rating>< Review>
1 check-in

After reading the reviews, I was hesitant to try out this place. But my cousin recommended this spot after he's valentine's day dinner with he's girlfriend. And I've been to their affiliate restaurants which were good.  So I thought to give them a try. I made reservations few weeks ahead and they called twice to confirm about the upcoming reservation. I instantly fell in love with patio area. It's beautiful sitting outside, enjoying drinks, hearing the water fountain especially in the beautiful weather like today. Perfect temperature.   Only  thing, I didn't like was our waitress, she was not attentive to our table. My husband ordered wine and the waitress forgot. We ordered appetizer and they delivered to the next table who arrived later but they had ordered exactly the same dish. And we had to ask for the dessert menu and wait for food and stuff long. I liked my salmon dish but my husbands pasta was salty. And we ordered bread pudding with rosemary. They gave lots of bread but a tiny scope of ice cream. And towards the end, I notice the couple who sat next to us, the waitress forgot to place the order for their meal. So the manager  came and apologized to them. The waitress was very forgetful.

They have street one hour parking until 6pm and valet parking lot. I like their bathrooms, it was nice and clean.< /Review>

< text>
Excellent. And I mean excellent interior design and layout. This place has style, charm, and comfort. And the food? Excellent too. I really enjoyed my lunch and visit. Checkout the menu as it will better describe the food than me but I can vouch that it's accurate in description. This is a local Sacramento family run restaurant that's well known in the area (there are other sister restaurants too). This is the new lead place. It's the type of place with good food where you can enjoy the environment with your company for a while. I like that as it helps foster an experience. It has a great indoor/outdoor al fresco european dining style that's sure to please. The wine list was also excellent and we had a couple of great bottles of pinot. When I'm up here, I'll be sure to visit as it's nice to know that you can have big city refined food and style up in Sacramento.<//text>

< user>
108764265938762534125< /user>
<name>Aida Orozco< /name><date>1492701111244< /date><Rating>3< /Rating>< text>
Went for Easter brunch. There was a limited menu,  but with good variety of options - steak and fries,  eggs Benedict,  Huevos rancheros or a Salmon salad. Brunch included a few pastries (very small samples) which were just okay. First course was a choice of yogurt & granola parfait or a choice of 3 salads.  Our table ordered the yogurt & granola and a seared salmon salad - both were good. The parfait was large with some fruit also, much of which was not quite ripe yet, but over all good. For the entree we ordered the steak and fries,  the Huevos rancheros and the Salmon salad, which all tasted good. Unfortunately though,  "the hot" meals came out cold... we saw earlier there seemed to be a little confusion as to which table some  plates were to go,  and the servers just took them back.  When I looked around, we seemed to be the only table in that dining area without our meals and it was several minutes later when our meals were finally served. I suggested sending the cold plates back,  but as we had already been waiting quite a long time,  they were hungry and just opted to eat the food. I did mention it to the server and later the manager came over and apologized, taking a little off the bill.  This was my companions first time at this restaurant (though they'd been to other Paragary's), and the managers apology and gesture may have saved losing a customer - one had already exclaimed that they wouldn't return.... As for me, though I haven't been to this location for quite a while,  I don't think this is the norm and would definitely return and give it a 2nd shot. It's a little pricey and you don't get huge portions, but you go for good food and service, and I think they know it.  I should mention,  they have a very nice patio with fireplace and water feature for dining also, but it was closed due to wet weather. Not sure about their bar, we had a michelada (hard to mess up) which wasn't very good - very blah, plain and another cocktail which was pretty good.</text>

< userid>
100374733894351000212<//userid>
< username>
Karen Gibson<//username>
<Date>1550728426285<//Date><rate>5<//rate>< Text>
One of my new, favorite places!
You would never notice this place if you were driving by. It's tucked into the tail end of a supermarket strip mall. From the outside, it's quite plain. Inside, it's very clean and bright.
We got there in the early afternoon, between lunch & dinnertime. I was happily surprised to find the food well-prepared, fresh, and there was a large selection of dishes.
The portions are big, the prices quite moderate. You can order from the menu, or choose from the steam table. I had the coconut shrimp, fried rice and noodles. My friend had a chicken dish. Both were delicious! I would do this again and again.
Service is quick, so if you want to dash in, pick up and take it home to eat, you can be in and out in minutes.
How could I have not heard of this place?<//Text>

<username>Morgan Brix<//username>< Rate>

< Text>
Fantastic deli quality subs with fresh fresh veggies! As far as quality of food, i would give 5 stars. My two gripes with the place is the speed in which the sandwiches are made and the size orientation of the sandwiches. First, all the meat is freshly sliced before its placed on the bread every time. Though it adds to that extra freshness, It can cause a lengthy wait time during busy hours. My biggest problem with the place is they only have 3 sizes. Small (4"), regular (8") and giant (16"). For me, if im hungry and i want a good sized sandwich, an 8 inch sub can leave me a little unsatisfied, but a 16 inch sub is way too much food and pricey. Id like to see them incorporate a large size like 10-12 inches. If none of that bothers you, then its definately a good sandwich chain to try.<//Text>

<username>Jay An</username>< text>
Whether you want to focus in weightlifting or CrossFit, Fortius is for you.

Being on the weightlifting side of the house, it is refreshing to find USAW-certified coaches who don't regard weightlifting as an afterthought, but it's own sport.

To be honest, I was adamantly opposed to CrossFit for years.  I was the first person to bash CrossFit for irresponsibly facilitating injuries through poor coaching, silly high-repetition Olympic movement workouts, and general clique-like, full-of-itself behavior.

That being said, the coaches at Fortius have completely flipped my view on CrossFit.  The coaches at Fortius prioritize safety above all else, and specifically program the CrossFit workouts to reduce needless injuries while promoting great all-around fitness.

One thing I love about this place it that there is an actual sense of community that includes everyone from beginners to competitors, and new members to the OG's.  Unlike some other places, there are no cliques at Fortius; you will receive coaching, make friends, and feel welcome whether it's your first workout of your life, or if you are CrossFit Games-bound.<//text>

The atmosphere is really great too. There's all different levels and athletes. Some people are here to get in shape, some are here to compete in Crossfit games, Olympic lifting, power lifting comps. And some of us have other sports on the side baseball, jiujitsu, basketball, triathletes, etc.

I've been at this gym for a little more than a year and although I take time off now and again I couldn't imagine going to another gym.

0x80dc0107b2e51c4f:0x2109718b59baafaf</Gmap_id>
<time>1370377190741< /time><username>Shannon Prager</username>< Review>
If you are considering trying crossfit, I would highly recommend that you try Crossfit Fortius!  I joined here 9 months ago and it was honestly the best decision I could have made after moving back to San Diego.  Even from my first day trying it out, I felt very welcomed and comfortable, but thankfully they offer you a whole week free to make sure it's the right fit for you.  I tried a couple of the other crossfit gyms around where I live, and none of them were offering a deal like that (you had to sign up after just one class) so it definitely was refreshing to see and certainly factored into my decision to join.  Another reason I joined was because everyone there was so friendly and welcoming.  People would always come up to me and introduce themselves and ask how I was liking it so far.  The community is definitely a big part of what keeps me coming back every day too.  Every one is so encouraging and pushes you to do your best during the workouts.  I've made so many great friends through Fortius and I love continuing to meet so many awesome people who share my passion for fitness and hardwork.

Not only is there an amazing community at Fortius, but the coaches are also extremely experienced and just plain awesome.  I've worked most closely with coach Jesse, and I am thankful every day to have a coach as wonderful as him.  When I first started doing crossfit, all of the Olympic weightlifting and powerlifting moves seemed extremely foreign and awkward to me and I didn't really like them, but Jesse has helped me with my technique and they now are starting to feel natural and I actually look forward to opportunities to practice them more.  He's always offering a helpful hint and encouraging word.  He pushes me to always do more than I think I can and because of him, I've hit a lot of personal records and already made so much progress.  When I first started, I would get winded after the 250m run, but now it seems like a breeze and my improved endurance helped to complete my first 5k only a few months later! It definitely also helps to improve your confidence, because after finishing a crazy WOD like Fran, Annie, or Murph, you feel like you can accomplish anything!

If you're worried about injuries or the workouts being too intense, don't be.  All of the moves can be modified to fit your skill level so that they are challenging, but not impossible.  For instance, I can't do strict pull-ups, so I use resistance bands as a modification, and over time, I have been able to use less and less resistance.  Also, the coaches are very careful to modify workouts for any injuries you may have so that you do not further injure yourself.

Before joining Fortius, I had a personal trainer and really enjoyed that, but I was finding it to be fairly expensive and wasn't getting the exact results that I wanted.  After trying crossfit, I found that it was quite similar to personal training, but a lot less expensive.  For the same price that I was paying for one 30 minute session once a week, I could get unlimited classes at Fortius.  So one 30 minute session per week or five hour long classes per week?  After realizing that, it wasn't very difficult to decide.  I was still getting a lot of the benefits of personal training (someone telling you what to do, accountability, personal attention since the classes are fairly small) but getting a lot more for my money and also getting the awesome community that comes with being a member at Fortius.

This ended up being a longer review than I expected, but simply put, you should definitely give Crossfit Fortius a try, you have nothing to lose and everything to gain!</Review>

<userid>114607294938873074479</userid><user_name>Wilmar Dumaop</user_name><date>1347477912854< /date><Rate>5</Rate><text>I have been with CrossFit Fortius since they opened their doors.  CFF is home to co-owners/Coaches Jesse and David and Coach Veronica.  All three have an extensive history with the sport of Olympic weightlifting, and are the best people to go to in San Diego to improve your weightlifting technique.

CFF runs two operations - the weightlifting club and the CrossFit classes.  As a member of the weightlifting club, I have access to four weightlifting platforms, competition-grade barbells and plates (Eleiko, Werksan, York, Mav-Rik), and immediate feedback from the coaches after I snatch, clean & jerk, squat, or whatever.  My girlfriend is a CrossFit member, and every day Coaches David and Jesse provide a structured program for her and the other members that focuses on functional movements, techniques, strength-building, and always contains a workout-of-the-day (a.k.a. WOD) that is high in intensity, but always scalable based on individual ability.

CFF is well-equipped to help you achieve your goals, whether it's for improving your overall health, to become a more explosive and productive player in whatever sport you do, or to get better at Olympic weightlifting.  In addition, training everyday at CFF has made me come to the conclusion that some of the best people I've ever met work out here.  We're all here to improve ourselves, and we do so in an inviting, encouraging, and focused environment.< /text><pics>None</pics>< resp>

103993982745563735046<//user_id>
< name>
Sarah Michael<//name>
<Time>1347479270697<//Time><Rate>5<//Rate>< text>
I started doing Crossfit here 2 months ago when they first opened up. I was incredibly skeptical about Crossfit (it's expensive, it seems REALLY difficult, I was intimidated by crossfitters in general), but I gave it a try because they had a free trial period. My first workout was REALLY difficult (I had not been constantly physically active for 8 years), but it was really fun. And I kept coming back! :)

Reasons why I love Crossfit Fortius:

1. The coaches are all top notch. I'm usually coached by Jesse, who is honestly one of the best coaches I've ever had (and I've had a good amount of decent coaches, I've played volleyball for several years). He's REALLY good at teaching you the different movements, he's incredibly patient, and he's really supportive. David and Veronica are EXCELLENT coaches as well. They all know their stuff and are focused on teaching the correct technique/building strength, not just teaching us how to do as many reps as possible.

2. Everyone at the gym is really cool. It's such a great environment to learn and exercise in; everyone is cheering everyone on, whether we are doing crossfit or weightlifting.

3. The workouts! Some are scarier than others, but they change daily to keep things interesting/work out all your muscle groups. Also, if there is ever a movement you can't do, it can be modified to your skill level (example: I can't do normal pullups, so I've been doing them with a resistance band). I also like the emphasis on learning the technique for olympic weighlifting, it's really helpful and fun!

4. Equipment: This place is decently equipped, plenty of space for pull ups, plenty of kettle bells of various weights, bars and plates, jump ropes, boxes for box jumps, ab mats, etc. They are also planning on getting some benches and j hooks for bench press, as well as a rowing machine.

Overall, I love everything about Crossfit Fortius. Great people, great coaches, and great workouts. I actually look forward to working out now :)<//text>

< Text>
When you hear Pacific Palisades all we can moot is that it‚Äôs the creme de la creme of views of the pacific ocean, cliffs and canyons. Palisades Bluffs Park is a small park in Pacific Palisades that offers impeccable view of the ocean and the coastal highway. It sits on a cliff overlooking the palisades residential area. Moreover, it has a modicum of concrete benches and trees. The highlight of my visit was when I saw a young deer down the cliff grazing the lush green bushes. It wasn‚Äôt crowded at all when I visited. Parking is available in the surrounding neighborhood. Overall, I think it‚Äôs a modest park with magnificent ocean view. I highly recommend you visit this park.</Text>

<Date>1587855923192<//Date>< Review>
Just a gorgeous morning above PCH. It's a beautiful view with morning mist. There is opportunity for a short walk and see all the beauty what mother nature offers. The best time to go, my experience,  is around 10 am. You can still see the mist, burns up a bit, and starts fog in (12 noon?). The slopes are steep so stay on track. Enjoy it along with  neighborhood flowers.<//Review>

< text>
As is the case with much of my travels, I found this place accidentally while randomly exploring the Palisades. I believe I personally enjoy this space because the scenery and views of the coastline and mountains from the Bluffs are insane and almost dramatic, like I'm in a primetime soap opera like Knots Landing and the neighbors meet at The Bluffs for a secret rendezvous or a cliffhanger-style (pun intended) confrontation. It would be cool to be a resident in this neighborhood just for the chances to hang out here on a regular basis.< /text>

We should've taken pictures.... But there are times and places where even a picture cannot contain such grandeur.  She stood up on the rail facing pch.... and as I held her by her hips, I told her to spread her arms and close her eyes.... As the wind blew through her dreadlocks and the pachouli swept from her skin and into my soul* she opened her eyes, and all she could see was everything.... She felt like one of the birds of the sky soaring above the Pacific ocean from Malibu to R.A.T. Beach.... She climbed down from the rail and into my arms.... And then it was my turn.  I flew too.  This is Our Spot... It can be urs too.üíéüåª‚úåÔ∏èüíùüíô<//Text>

<time>1614834142945</time>< Rate>

<review>5 Diamond Mechanical was excellent. I live in a high rise and the AC unit was custom designed and built for my building. I called 5 Diamond Mechanical and they were able to send a technician the same day. The technician was very professional, he ran diagnostics on my AC unit and was able to give me options on how to proceed. I knew that what I really needed was a new AC unit since mine was 19 years old. They were able to get one of the custom AC units from the manufacturer, since other homeowners were also replacing their units and the manufacturer makes these in batches. In just a couple of days 5 Diamond Mechanical installed my new unit. They even installed a complementary Nest thermostat. I am very happy with their service and I will definitely recommend them to my neighbors who may need to replace their units. I will also be using their services again in the future for the maintenance of my unit.< /review><pictures>None<//pictures>< Resp>

<Review>This is my review based on this one experience. I‚Äôve been before without the issues we had this time, but I will likely not return anytime soon.
Had a drink at the bar without any issues while waiting for a table.
The table took longer than quoted, but not by too much and it was a Friday evening, so somewhat expected. I think the process for having guests check back in once notified could be improved, especially when busy. There was no clear spot for us to return, so we waited in line with people adding their names to the list.
Once seated, we were greeted warmly and promptly, but when it came time to order drinks, it was clear the server was not well-versed in the available options. We asked about flavored spirits and the server just named brands, not flavors. When we asked for something listed as as an ingredient in a specialty cocktail, she said they didn‚Äôt have it. When the drink arrived, it wasn‚Äôt made correctly and the replacement took an unusually long time.
Now to the food.  I started with a side salad, which, while it looked appealing, had a pool of water at the bottom and was drenched in gloppy ranch dressing.
The pot pie I ordered was decent and the others at the table enjoyed their entrees, but they weren‚Äôt anything special.

<text>This is a gluten free review.

Gluten free menu: Yes! Request a gluten free menu when you are being seated

What I ordered: I did the unconventional and ordered gluten free carrot cake before my meal, followed by a Cobb salad and French fries

Gluten free options: 3/5
Super impressed that they have a gluten free cake. This is not your average gluten free dessert, but it‚Äôs made with almond flour and was absolutely incredible.

Food: 4/5
I was impressed with the cake and the fried. The salad was short on a lot of toppings. It was 90% lettuce and 10% toppings. Felt a little jipped this time around when it came to the salad. The rest of the meal was amazing though, which is why I can justify this rating. They really do have the best French fries. Perfectly crispy!

Service: 2/5
Our server was friendly but not attentive. It took about 15 mins to receive the cake. We also were never asked for a water refill. I also noticed that most of the servers congregate near the bar, are talking, laughing, and then they disperse at around the same time. Not really efficient for taking care of their customers.

Location: 4/5
Parking is abundant and the restaurant is easy to locate

Ambiance: 3/5
Casual and comfortable environment. You can bring your dog to eat on the patio.

Price: 4/5
$37 for two people. Two entrees, appetizer, no drinks. Not bad!

Overall score: 4/5< /text>< Pics>

<Date>1546729009755</Date><Rate>5< /Rate><review>I cannot say enough about the staff here. They are absolutely amazing! We have been having a rough 24 hours with our pooch Titus and decided to bring him here after the ER visit to help settle our nerves and get him some food as well. So many friendly people, including staff, were asking about our dog because the recent shavings he received are very noticeable. < Text>
Excellent service!!!  A BIG THANK YOU to the management team at Lazy Dog in Irvine.  I was planning a Baby Reveal at the restaurant and Karim and Jake were very helpful in every way. < Text>
This is a slightly pricier restaurant offering American fare, much along the lines of Cheesecake Factory. However, this restaurant has a cozier, friendlier feel. Maybe it has to do with their policy of allowing dogs to eat with you on the outside patio (none are allowed inside, so you can enjoy your food dog-allergy-free if that applies). In any case, their food options are solid. The pot roast and chicken pot pie come highly recommended. Service is excellent. Parking can be a bit tricky at peak meal times, and there can be a wait as well.< /Text>

< Review>
Average food with mediocre service.
I've been many times and it's stayed true to form. The atmosphere is really pretty cool its always fun to see the different dogs that are there. However, that really only goes so far. The food has never been "bad", but I've never had excellent either. Seasoning, doneness, temperature, something is always just not quite right. Not enough to complain about, but never where you're excited about what you just got either. As for the service, I don't know if they have too much rotation or just hire the servers that aren't on their A-game, but again it's never quite what you expect. Either they walk by you several times when you're drinks are empty, they don't know the menu, or just seem too busy... Will I go back again? Yeah, I'm sure I will. But it's never at the top of my list, it's more like "well, we could go to Lazy Dog, we haven't been in awhile".</Review>

We were seated within 5 minutes, it seemed busy too. Ordered our appetizer and 2 entrees and it arrived within 15 mins. Fast friendly servise. The manager gave us free cheesy flat bread for out first time there and another manager gave us a coupon for free desert or appetizer on our next visit. The waitress was quick and consistent as weel. When it gets busy the service level on things like refills, clearing your table, getting your check declines. But generally it is good. Servers typically are smiling and friendly and always smiling.

They have a very varied menu. Tons of things to select from and interesting unique items as well. They put unique touches on things such as the quesadilla where they brown the cheese on the outside of the tortilla in addition to the filling.

I think they have some of the best fish and chips around. Nice thick pieces of cod. The cole slaw and fries are great too with this dish. The other item I love is the breaded pork chop.

Their corn wheel seasonal appetizer is great. Like getting Mexican street corn (elotes)

Nice ambiance and you can bring your dog to sit outside and dine on the patio<//Review><Rate>4</Rate></record></dataset><record>

<time>1458686417752</time><text>I took my wife for a lunch at the restaurant last weekend, this is maybe the 5th. or 6th. time to go there, but it will be the last for sure.  We waited for about 20 minutes to be seated which is fine as they looked quite busy. But we were seated outside as requested but we were seated in the sun. My wife asked the waiter to see if we could be moved to another table that had just become vacant and Seth the waiter was very polite and moved us to the shady table.  He came after a few minutes and said that we might have to move back to the other table because he was told by his manager to send us back as that table was going to be giving to a different party and we may have move back to the table in the sun.  He came back again and told us that we COULD stay as he "fought for us".  I really did not like the idea I called the manager and told him that as a courtesy to the customer they should have kept their seating problem away from the customer I did not have to feel any stress because of their seating situation, he said that he was going to let us stay on the current table in a tune made me feel that he was doing us a favor!! I told him that he was not doing me any favor. And to be honest this may not sound a big deal, but we both felt awkward and were not going to stay if we were told we had to move back.
We are not going back to this location, but we love the location in Orange as well as Brea

< review>
I took my wife for a lunch at the restaurant last weekend, this is maybe the 5th. or 6th. time to go there, but it will be the last for sure.  We waited for about 20 minutes to be seated which is fine as they looked quite busy. But we were seated outside as requested but we were seated in the sun. My wife asked the waiter to see if we could be moved to another table that had just become vacant and Seth the waiter was very polite and moved us to the shady table.  He came after a few minutes and said that we might have to move back to the other table because he was told by his manager to send us back as that table was going to be giving to a different party and we may have move back to the table in the sun.  He came back again and told us that we COULD stay as he "fought for us".  I really did not like the idea I called the manager and told him that as a courtesy to the customer they should have kept their seating problem away from the customer I did not have to feel any stress because of their seating situation, he said that he was going to let us stay on the current table in a tune made me feel that he was doing us a favor!! I told him that he was not doing me any favor. And to be honest this may not sound a big deal, but we both felt awkward and were not going to stay if we were told we had to move back.
We are not going back to this location, but we love the location in Orange as well as Brea
Mohamed Anwar<//review>
